About 1913.

97th Atreet, Amsterdam to Columbia Avenue, front of #119.
(Before Reconstruction)

 September 30, 1921.

161-169 West 97th Street, north side, east of Amsterdam Avenue.

P.L. Sperr.

Shanley's restaurant occupies Nos. 163-165 and was demolished in 1931. This with the adjoining structure (167) was sold as per New York Times of December 15, 1938. The latter housed a boys club; title being transferred by the R.C. Church of the Holy Name. The New York Sun of July 10, 1939 reports the proposed erection of a six-story elevator apartment house here.

97th-100th Streets between Amsterdam Avenue and Central Park West, Manhattan.
"Manhattantown" site, now known as West Park.

Photographs taken November 1953; all buildings now demolished.

Elinor G. Black, photographer, N.Y.C.
Received as gift, 1973.
